The paper deals with topics related to information theory, randomness, and dimension, which are typically studied in the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of constructive Hausdorff dimension and finite-state dimensions suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the similarity of probability measures, which is a topic studied in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The compression characterizations of dimensions suggest a connection to the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the use of Kullback-Leibler divergence suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
